<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,525,551]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body rather narrow and subparallel-sided elongate; elytra distinctly striate; head gradually narrowed to base, with rather small and extremely finely faceted eyes located rather anteriorly; prothoracic lateral carinae comparatively expressed and visible from above; pronotal anterior angles with narrowly rounded (subangular) tip; scutellar shield subtriangular; all tibiae moderately wide and moderately dorsoventrally compressed (not swollen at apex) and without group of short and thick spines at apex; femora moderately wide, thick; tarsi with narrowly lobed tarsomeres 1–3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,538,741,767]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Notes on systematic position</emphasis>
. This new taxon is proposed for a group of species rather similar to the species of 
<emphasis box="[181,356,777,803]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[181,291,777,803]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Adocimus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[298,356,778,803]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with the 
<typeStatus box="[458,506,778,804]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1664" box="[622,719,777,804]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[622,719,777,804]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">A. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the crucial differences between the former and latter consist mostly in the presence or absence of the prothoracic carinae, structure of head, shape of prothorax and structures legs segments. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1664" box="[324,510,849,875]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[324,510,849,875]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Adocimus bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and closest still undescribed species, in contrast to other cillaeines, have swollen prothoracic sides which demonstrate only lateral rollers in places where the lateral carinae are located in other groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Both these groups (
<emphasis box="[416,591,957,983]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[416,526,957,983]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Adocimus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[532,591,958,983]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[754,866,957,983]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[754,866,957,983]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[872,1019,957,983]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[872,1019,957,983]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) are very similar and seem to be very closely related to each other. Taking into consideration diversity of both them, including undescribed species, many their characters show parallel transformations and, as a result, these taxa can be distinguished only by the characters indicated in the above key to Australian cilaeine genera and subgenera and above diagnosis. It necessary to add that different species of the new subgenus and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[698,819,1101,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,819,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(including undescibed species) show many structural parallelisms and their hiatus is the most distinctly expressed in the structures of head (length, position of eyes, expression of antennal grooves), while the lateral carinae of the prothorax and tibiae in some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[1170,1291,1173,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1170,1291,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also very similar to those in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[357,469,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[357,469,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[475,622,1209,1235]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[475,622,1209,1235]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The subgeneric rank of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[891,1003,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[891,1003,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1009,1156,1209,1235]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1009,1156,1209,1235]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is rather preliminary and it can be changed after a further wider revision of both 
<emphasis box="[764,940,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[764,874,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Adocimus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[881,940,1246,1271]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[993,1105,1245,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[993,1105,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1111,1258,1245,1271]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1111,1258,1245,1271]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
At this moment it can be noted that the widely distributed 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[631,743,1281,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[631,743,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[751,899,1281,1307]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[751,899,1281,1307]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seems to be most generalized, apparently quite numerous in species but not very variable in structures and apparently with the greatest number of plesiomorphic characters. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[278,399,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Ithyphenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,399,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Ithyphenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most diverse in structures and number of species and rather wide in its range. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1864" box="[1301,1411,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Adocimus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="20" pageNumber="21" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is the most specialized and rather small group, which is rather uniform in structures, showing many apomorphic characters and very restricted in the distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1461,1487]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of this genus is formed from the Greek βελόνη (“spearhead”, “spike”, “needle”) and suffix “ 
<emphasis box="[235,268,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">tus</emphasis>
”. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1533,1559]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Composition</emphasis>
. This subgenus includes two described species (
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[897,1258,1533,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartenevi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[897,1007,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Adocimus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1024,1136,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belonotus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1152,1258,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">bartenevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1266,1357,1533,1560]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1266,1350,1533,1559]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirejtshuk &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Grouvelle" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Adocimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidulus" status="comb. nov." subGenus="Belonotus">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[161,178,1570,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[201,299,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">nitidulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[306,436,1569,1596]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[306,429,1569,1595]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(? = 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grouvelle" authorityYear="1897" box="[487,616,1569,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Cillaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modiglianii">
<emphasis box="[487,616,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">modiglianii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), although some species of it are still waiting for description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,525,1667]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1605,1631]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution</emphasis>
. Widely spread through the Indo-Malayan and Australian regions and apparently with most diversity in Sunda Islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
